{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/demystifying-hyper-parameter-tuning-acb83af0258f", "time": 1682993764.162831, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/demystifying-hyper-parameter-tuning-acb83af0258f/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Demystifying Hyper-Parameter tuning | by Charles Brecque | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Demystifying Hyper-Parameter tuning", "description": "Hyper-parameters structure many every day processes but few people are aware of their existence. When you are looking for a pair of shoes to buy, you are solving a hyper-parameter optimization\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://medium.com/u/e2f299e30cb9?source=post_page-----acb83af0258f--------------------------------", "anchor_text": "William Koehrsen", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/hyperparameter-tuning-the-random-forest-in-python-using-scikit-learn-28d2aa77dd74", "anchor_text": "article", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://mindfoundry.ai", "anchor_text": "Mind Foundry", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://www.mindfoundry.ai/learning-hub/the-intuitions-behing-bayesian-optimization", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://www.mindfoundry.ai/cs/c/?cta_guid=d52ed367-1cd3-4575-b184-1187ffce8e81&placement_guid=b1db3f2f-f3fd-49a9-bf8a-e814a2ed2dce&portal_id=5481365&canon=https://www.mindfoundry.ai/mind-foundry-optimize&redirect_url=APefjpHbWc7SuBgpfkLUwmAk1AxrZxmiyd-siCDKkwoeIXeOR-a3glPowXzPjGf2Q8ruEKQNEbuY6ip1Z5u58kVvOv7jLJpJTlsFQhUfSVcJL9CoDQtUG2YOcVHxwVIft5TlDg5vccCjP-hVeBQjdAXk7Fkrir7WFFsasPXps0kyarGzgAHilw-0rrnzG4BodeJYIPFEgnAKeFerSqxXFtnSc5AbVBFVFJCpqT3gRZfe4bYKwkkTNuFk7izVnzNN8t2TF6pQF0drkRDG0eXAGKovmJr1FECiD45SGHjTZT3yOZFYxoxSb-Y&click=d024b0b0-a11e-4644-a78e-2af3926dfdd3&hsutk=a05abc5c609da99dcc92da7a1a0a916c&utm_referrer=https://www.mindfoundry.ai/&pageId=9198035490&__hstc=41946106.a05abc5c609da99dcc92da7a1a0a916c.1558293272861.1558293272861.1558293272861.1&__hssc=41946106.2.1558293272861&__hsfp=672623401", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 16}, {"url": "http://www.legislate.tech/", "anchor_text": "company", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://medium.com/legislate/eliminate-the-work-in-paperwork-c053bfb0188c", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://mindfoundry.ai/wp-content/uploads/optaas-2-pager.pdf", "anchor_text": "through intelligent batching", "paragraph_index": 18}, {"url": "https://optaas.mindfoundry.ai", "anchor_text": "certain", "paragraph_index": 20}, {"url": "https://legislate.ai", "anchor_text": "https://legislate.ai", "paragraph_index": 22}], "all_paragraphs": ["Hyper-parameters structure many every day processes but few people are aware of their existence. When you are looking for a pair of shoes to buy, you are solving a hyper-parameter optimization problem. Once you have decided which type of shoes you are going to buy (hyper-parameter) you need to fit the parameters of the shoes to meet your requirements (size, colour,\u2026). Your available budget is also a hyper-parameter that will affect your choices.", "If you chose a pair of shoes that fits you and is the right colour you will be able to wear them. However, you might find running a marathon challenging if you chose a pair of red stilettos. Hyper-parameter tuning might not be critical for most use cases but can significantly affect the efficiency of your processes and the quality of the results you are trying to obtain (e.g. you can run in boots but you might not run as fast as with trainers).", "Most Machine Learning models have hyper-parameters.", "For example, a simple random forest algorithm will have quite a few:", "Once a user has specified the values of its hyper-parameters, the algorithm will be trained on the underlying data set. The choice of the hyper-parameters will affect the duration of the training and the accuracy of the predictions. Unfortunately, choosing hyper-parameters isn\u2019t straight forward as the number of possible configurations explodes with their number and the evaluation time of a configuration is function of the complexity of the model and the size of the underlying training data. Moreover, it is a bit of a dark art and as William Koehrsen put perfectly in his Medium article:", "Hyperparameter tuning relies more on experimental results than theory, and thus the best method to determine the optimal settings is to try many different combinations evaluate the performance of each model.", "With so much uncertainty it is understandable that most Data Scientists forego hyper-parameter tuning and stick with the default values provided by the model. This works in most cases, but to pick up on my introductory analogy, you might struggle to run a marathon in stilettos.", "You wouldn\u2019t do it in real life (unless it was for a good cause), so why would you in Data Science?", "The second most popular approach is to find the optimal configuration through grid-search (evaluating every single configuration) which will evantually lead to an answer.", "But you wouldn\u2019t run a marathon with every single pair of shoes you own to conclude that you get the best results with trainers, so why would you do the same in Data Science?", "The third most popular approach is to find the optimal configuration through random-search, but this is only marginally better than grid-search. I\u2019ll spare you with an analogy for this one as I hope by now you see my point.", "So how can hyper-parameter tuning be done more efficiently?", "Mind Foundry\u2019s Twitter followers seem to know the answer", "Bayesian Optimization addresses the pitfalls of grid and random search by incorporating a \u201cbelief\u201d of what the solution space looks like, and by \u201clearning\u201d from the configurations it evaluates. This belief can be specified by a domain expert but can also be flat at the beginning. If and when you try to run a marathon in stilettos, you won\u2019t try it again with every other pair of stilletos you own because you will have learnt that it\u2019s painful. Moreover, if you had prior knowledge, you might have chosen flat soled shoes right from the beginning!", "I have written a more detailed article (with less analogies) explaining the intuitions behing Bayesian Optimization here:", "A downloadable white-paper version can be found here.", "You can automatically receive an API key for our Bayesian Optimizer, OPTaaS, here!", "[UPDATE: I have started a tech company. You can find out more here]", "If you have friends who can try other pairs of shoes, you will collectively find the best pair to run a marathon with faster. The same can be achieved in BO through intelligent batching.", "If you are running a marathon in stilettos, you should (in theory) realise fairly early on that it\u2019s rather painful and you should just stop and change shoes?", "Well, this is possible in certain implementations of Bayesian Optimization and in my next article, I will explain how.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Charles Brecque is the Founder and CEO of Legislate. Find out more: https://legislate.ai"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Facb83af0258f&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdemystifying-hyper-parameter-tuning-acb83af0258f&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdemystifying-hyper-parameter-tuning-acb83af0258f&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?so